Package: Proteopedia
Title: Streamlined Analysis Tooklit for Post-Acquisition Proteomic Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Date: 2026-07-15
Authors@R: 
    person("Jonathan", "Meyrick", , "jonathanj.meyrick@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Jonathan Meyrick <jonathanj.meyrick@gmail.com>
Description: Package contains functions which can be appled to outputs from DIA-NN acquisition of proteomic data. This
    includes label-free or pulse-SILAC data. Functions automate analysis of conditional comparisons, standardising analysis 
    from DIA-NN to protein- and ontology-level outputs. This toolkit is recommended for newer proteomics users, to rapidly
    analyse data, or proteomic facilities for high-throughput data processing.
Depends: arrow, BiocGenerics, clusterProfiler, data.table, DescTools, DOSE, dplyr, enrichplot, forcats, ggplot2, ggrepel, 
    ggside, ggupset, grid, highcharter, htmlwidgets, imputeLCMD, iq, limma, mzR, minpack.lm, nlme, org.Hs.eg.db, patchwork, 
    Peptides, ReactomePA, stats, stringr, tidyr
